<div class="row resource">
	<div class="span6">
		<h3>Faculty Affairs</h3>
		<p>Faculty Affairs is responsible for faculty teaching certifications, conflict of interest and commitment policy development and review, and for the facilitation of professional development opportunities including faculty mentoring initiatives, workshops, and the promotion and tenure process. Visit the <a href="http://facultyaffairs.ucf.edu" target="_blank">Faculty Affairs website</a></p>
	</div>
	<div class="span3">
		<img class="alignnone size-medium wp-image-216" style="float: right" src="http://provost.ucf.edu/files/2011/01/faculty-resources11-300x185.jpg" alt="Students and Professor standing around table with clay pots."  />
	</div>
</div>
<div class="row resource">
	<div class="span6">
		<h3>Faculty Center for Teaching and Learning</h3>
		<p>The Faculty Center for Teaching and Learning collaborates with faculty members to encourage excellence in classroom teaching and engagement in pedagogical research by offering a variety of services including conferences, consultations, workshops, book clubs, and professional development opportunities. Visit the <a href="http://www.fctl.ucf.edu/">Faculty Center for Teaching and Learning website</a>.</p>
	</div>
	<div class="span3">
		<img class="alignnone size-medium wp-image-898" style="float: right" src="http://provost.ucf.edu/files/2010/12/FCTL-300x185.jpg" alt=""  />
	</div>
</div>
<div class="row resource">
	<div class="span6">
		<h3>Faculty Relations</h3>
		<p>The Office of Faculty Relations works largely with faculty concerns. These involve collective bargaining, grievances, discipline/termination, investigations, non-reappointments, layoffs, and other faculty-related issues. Visit the <a href="http://www.facultyrelations.ucf.edu/" target="_blank">Faculty Relations website.</a></p>
	</div>
	<div class="span3">

	</div>
</div>
